FDefectDesc_EN: The machining of OP4000 surface for DTA2003037 was completed on Milling Machine No. 6. During tool change, it was discovered that tool 52306 was broken, specifically at the 26th hole. The chamfer on the back of the skirt flange hole was not machined from the 26th to the 49th hole in a counterclockwise direction. There were several dents on the hub surface corresponding to the 25th and 26th holes. The cutting fluid did not stop flowing, and the broken tool has been collected.
Fqccomments_EN: It has been confirmed that there are 3 dent scrach on the hub surface corresponding to holes 25-26 on the non-balanced surface. The largest dent scrach area, labeled as 1#, is measured. The data is attached. The process is suspended pending QA's handling. On December 6, 2025, QA and Lihong responded on TEAMS that DA information needs to be updated: all holes and chamfers are visually inspected as OK, with no embedded objects. On December 15, 2025, the DA was updated. According to the rework order, the rework results are OK, visually inspected as OK, and the dimensions are OK. On December 23, 2025
Root cause of occurrence: only one case, root cause still under investigation
